  "prompt": "How do I communicate with my wife so she stops complaining and sending me no good vibes?",
  "response": "Open and empathetic communication is key to improving your relationship and addressing your wife's complaints or negative feelings. Here are some steps to approach the situation constructively:\n\n1. **Choose the Right Time and Place**  \n   Initiate the conversation when both of you are calm and not distracted. Avoid discussing sensitive issues during heated moments.\n\n2. **Listen Actively**  \n   When she shares her feelings, listen without interrupting, judging, or getting defensive. Show genuine interest and try to understand her perspective. For example, say, \u201cI hear that you\u2019re feeling frustrated. Can you help me understand what\u2019s causing that?\u201d\n\n3. **Acknowledge Her Feelings**  \n   Validate her emotions, even if you don\u2019t fully agree. Say something like, \u201cI can see why you\u2019d feel that way, and I\u2019m sorry you\u2019re feeling this way.\u201d\n\n4. **Express Your Feelings Calmly**  \n   Share how her complaints or negative vibes affect you without blaming her. Use \u201cI\u201d statements, such as, \u201cI feel overwhelmed when there\u2019s a lot of negativity because I care about us being happy together.\u201d\n\n5. **Ask for Specifics**  \n   Gently ask her what she needs or expects from you. For example, \u201cWhat can I do to help improve things between us?\u201d This shows you\u2019re willing to work on the relationship.\n\n6. **Collaborate on Solutions**  \n   Work together to find ways to address the issues. Ask, \u201cHow can we both approach this differently so we feel more connected?\u201d\n\n7. **Focus on Positive Interactions**  \n   Make an effort to bring positivity into your interactions. Compliment her, express gratitude, or engage in activities you both enjoy.\n\n8. **Be Patient and Consistent**  \n   Changing patterns takes time. Show her through your actions that you\u2019re committed to improving the relationship.\n\n9. **Consider Professional Help**  \n   If communication remains challenging, consider couples counseling. A therapist can help you both navigate underlying issues and improve your connection.\n\nRemember, the goal isn\u2019t to \u201cstop her from complaining\u201d but to create a healthier dynamic where both of you feel heard, valued, and supported.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
